# Install Obot Skill

Use this flow to determine which skill to install:

- If the user did not provide an argument, ask which skill they want to install, then continue with their response.
- If the user provided a skill ID, install that skill directly. Skill IDs start with `sk1`, such as `sk1abc123` or `sk1-default-github-review-a1b2c3d4`.
- If the user provided anything other than a skill ID, use it as a search query:

```sh
obot skills search --non-interactive "<query>"
```

Handle the search results this way:

- If there are no results, tell the user no matching skills were found.
- If there is one result, ask the user whether they want to install it.
- If there is more than one result, ask the user which skill they want to install.

When a skill has been selected, run the Obot CLI install command for this client:

```sh
obot skills install --non-interactive --destination {{ .InstallDestination }} <skill>
```

Report the CLI result to the user.
